<div>
  <h2>
    <small>Interflux presents:</small>
    <strong>Low Melting Point Alloys</strong>
  </h2>
  <div id="guage">
    {{temperature-gauge process=process}}
  </div>
  <div id="processes">
    <div class="wave" {{action 'setProcess' 'wave'}}>
      <img src="/assets/images/wave-soldering.jpg" alt="wave soldering icon">
      <h3>Wave soldering</h3>
      <p>LMPA-Q: 200°C - 230°C</p>
      <p>Sn(Ag)Cu: 260°C - 280°C</p>
    </div>
    <div class="selective" {{action 'setProcess' 'selective'}}>
      <img src="/assets/images/selective-soldering.jpg" alt="selective soldering icon">
      <h3>Selective soldering</h3>
      <p>LMPA-Q: 200°C - 250°C</p>
      <p>Sn(Ag)Cu: 270°C - 320°C</p>
    </div>
    <div class="reflow" {{action 'setProcess' 'reflow'}}>
      <img src="/assets/images/reflow-soldering.jpg" alt="reflow soldering icon">
      <h3>Reflow soldering</h3>
      <p>LMPA-Q: 190°C - 220°C</p>
      <p>Sn(Ag)Cu: 235°C - 250°C</p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <h2>What does
    <strong>LMPA</strong>
    <nobr>stand for?</nobr>
  </h2>
  <p>
    <strong>LMPA<sup>&trade;</sup>
    </strong>
    is short for
    <strong>Low Melting Point Alloys</strong>
    <sup>&trade;</sup>
    developed by
    <a href="http://www.interflux.com" target="_blank">Interflux<sup>&reg;</sup>
      Electronics NV</a>. These alloys enable soldering temperatures that are considerably lower than for the traditional lead-free Sn(Ag)Cu (SAC) alloys.</p>
  <p>
    <strong>
      <nobr>LMPA<sup>&trade;</sup>-Q</nobr>
    </strong>
    is an enhanced LMPA<sup>&trade;</sup>
    with superior mechanical properties. The benefits are numerous:</p>
  <h3>Benefits</h3>
  <ul id="benefits">
    <li>
      {{#link-to 'locale.speed'}}
        {{svg-check}}
        <span>5 times faster soldering with zero defect</span>
      {{/link-to}}
    </li>
    <li>
      {{#link-to 'locale.voiding'}}
        {{svg-check}}
        <span>Reduce voiding below 10%</span>
      {{/link-to}}
    </li>
    <li>
      {{#link-to 'locale.costs'}}
        {{svg-check}}
        <span>Lower production costs &amp; increase line capacity</span>
      {{/link-to}}
    </li>
    <li>
      {{#link-to 'locale.heat-failures'}}
        {{svg-check}}
        <span>Avoid heat-related board and component failures</span>
      {{/link-to}}
    </li>
    <li>
      {{#link-to 'locale.dross'}}
        {{svg-check}}
        <span>Drastically reduce dross formation (oxides)</span>
      {{/link-to}}
    </li>
    <li>
      {{#link-to 'locale.wetting'}}
        {{svg-check}}
        <span>Achieve excellent wetting</span>
      {{/link-to}}
    </li>
  </ul>
  <h3>Processes</h3>
  <p>LMPA<sup>&trade;</sup>-Q can be used for all soldering processes:</p>
  <ul id="processes">
    <li><img src="/assets/images/wave-soldering.jpg" alt="wave soldering icon">For wave soldering</li>
    <li><img src="/assets/images/selective-soldering.jpg" alt="selective soldering icon">For selective soldering</li>
    <li><img src="/assets/images/reflow-soldering.jpg" alt="reflow soldering icon">For reflow soldering</li>
  </ul>
</div>
